Subject: Re: [T2] door panels

I re-glued my vapor barrier after replacing the window regulator.  I am at
work now but can look for the tube when I get home.  I just picked it up at a
hardware store and looked for something weather proof, plastic friendly, and
versatile.  For the speakers, get some sheet plastic (I even used cut up
garbage bags) and glue the to the vapor barrier above the speakers and tuck
the plastic around them and into the door hollow.  This will create a little
roof over the speakers and drain the water back to the door instead of near
the cardboard panel.  Then glue the vapor barrier back to the doorframe.  You
may also want to check this thread:
http://www.thesamba.com/vw/forum/viewtopic.php?t=445486&highlight=vapor

Erik
